test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7de1be5c56c0>([42])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7de1be5c56c0> = [[1, 42], [1, 42, 1], [42], [42, 1], [1, 42], [1, 42, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7de1be5c56c0>([1, 42])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7de1be5c56c0> = [[1, 42], [1, 42, 1], [42], [42, 1], [1, 42], [1, 42, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7de1be5c56c0>([42, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7de1be5c56c0> = [[1, 42], [1, 42, 1], [42], [42, 1], [1, 42], [1, 42, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 42
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
